title.69: Peter Parker, the Spectacular Spider-Man Annual (1979) #9

description.0: First the Silver Surfer had to battle the In-Betweener, then he had to face Starfox, and now he has to deal with the ongoing Kree/Skrull war!
description.2: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #124. ""Play With Me."" Arcade's deranged ""Murderworld"" turns on its creator. A peek inside the mind of the X-Men's most maniacal foe!
description.3: The Green Goblin returns! And to save his family he must fight the Hobgoblin! To make matters worse, Spidey's caught in the middle! And to complicate things even more, the events of Inferno could push Harry Osborn beyond the brink of insanity!
description.4: Reed and Sue Richards attack the Orphan-Maker and Nanny for the safe return of their son, Franklin. Kang watches the battle from the surface of the time bubble, and debates his involvement. After Franklin is secured in the arms of his parents, the Fantastic Four agree to help Cap re-form the Avengers team.
description.5: It's a bloody civil war! Captain America versus Captain America! After months of manipulation from the resurrected Red Skull, Steve Rogers finally confronts his replacement as Captain America: John Walker! Don't miss this gigantic issue!
description.14: Conan— a slave?! Maybe for now. But as anyone who's familiar with the savage Cimmerian knows, Conan's not going to take that kind of treatment lying down!
description.15: Death's Head was last up against the Dragon's Claws team. We know how that turned out. Now, he's back and ready to take down Scavenger!
description.19: A super-team SMACKDOWN! The NIGHT SHIFT has come for the West Coast Avengers - and only one team will walk away!
description.21: All hail Dormammu, Sorcerer Supreme!? The dread demon has taken hold of Strange's body, and only his beloved Clea can save him!
description.25: A new Star Brand is born! Jacob Burnley has been gifted with the Star Brand's power, but what happened to the original Star Brand, Ken Connell?
description.26: The effects of INFERNO hit the world of Spider-Man! Peter's pal Harry Osborn is in grave danger at his chemical plant!
description.27: A cat-hating supervillain turns Speedball’s world upside down in "The Two-Legged Rat"!
description.29: The manhunt for Matt continues! Typhoid returns to finish what she started- but what if Black Widow and Karen find Daredevil first? DD is visited by a figure from his past, but is it enough to ward off death?
description.30: Captain Britain's ex-flame Courtney Ross, kidnapped by Arcade! Brian Braddock swings into action when the woman he once loved, and may still love, is up for ransom. But Courtney proves she's not quite the damsel in distress the team believes her to be! Excalibur enters Murderworld.
description.31: It's the blockbuster conclusion of the "Atlantis Attacks" epic! Llyra, Ghaur, and Attuma are at the height of their power! Will Set finally seize control of the Earth? What can the Fantastic Four and the Sub-Mariner possibly do to shatter the Serpent Crown and stop Set's rule?
description.32: After battling in the Evolutionary War, the Hulk takes a nap in his Las Vegas apartment. And the dream he has while he slumbers is no ordinary dream, but rather another adventure!
description.33: The Rhino breaks Donald Gill, aka Blizzard, out of jail. After day of doing chores like making amends with Steve Rogers, Tony Stark suits up and incapacitates the Rhino. The Blizzard, however, escapes!
description.35: Chapter IX in the "Atlantis Attacks" crossover saga! Attuma's finally got the power to do what he's always desired - annihilate Atlantis! How can the New Mutants stop him? Guest-starring Namorita! Plus: Boom Boom goes on the Dating Game TV show!
description.37: The All-Father lives! Imprisoned by Seth, Odin lies beneath the Black Pyramid, and Thor has come at last to free him! But suddenly, a new threat looms--the horrible demon known only as Surtur!
description.42: Graviton is wreaking havoc in the streets of New York, and it's up to the Human Torch to stop him - alone! Can Johnny come out on top without the help of the rest of the Four?
description.45: After the battle with the In-Betweener, Galactus must feed! Nova is sent to find a planet for her master to feast upon, but when Firelord and Starfox arrive, even the Silver Surfer might not be able to stand against their might!
description.49: When Atlantean forces assume control of a handful of U.S. military bases, Captain America assembles the Avengers West Coast and reserves to do battle with them.
description.50: ATLANTIS ATTACKS continues! Seven super heroes are in the running to be the bride of an unborn god...but entirely against their wills!
description.51: The Earth has but twelve hours to live. Twelve hours before a menace from beyond the solar system consumes it and its four billion inhabitants. Earth's only hope is the band of self-appointed superhuman champions who once called themselves the Squadron Supreme. Hyperion, the strongest man on Earth! Power Princess, the genetically engineered woman warrior! Dr. Spectrum, master of the alien power prism! The Whizzer, the fastest man in the world! Arcanna, mistress of the mystic arts! Redstone, the invulnerable mountain of muscle! Lady Lark, winged singer of hypersonic songs! The Shape, a man with a body of pliant putty! Haywire, spinner of psychoplasmic string! Inertia, manipulator of a fundamental force! But will the sum total of humanity's superhuman power be great enough to repulse the planet's extra-dimensional executioner? Join Earth's hard-pressed heroes in their ultimate challenge...a desperate race against the cosmic clock with the fate of the world hanging in the balance! Join...the Squadron Supreme!
description.53: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #123. ""Motherland."" Colossus returns home to Russia but is soon called into action when local disaster strikes.
description.55: Death's Head is now fully operational! Too bad he's got to do his first job for free!
description.57: Inferno's taking over Manhattan! An innocent man dies trying to save Spidey! And waiting malevolently in the wings is...Mysterio!
description.58: When Atlantean forces assume control of a handful of U.S. military bases, Captain America assembles the Avengers West Coast and reserves to do battle with them.
description.59: After hordes of demons attack the city, remaining Avenger Captain America calls on the New Mutants for assistance. But what do Nanny and the Orphan-Maker have to do with the villainous swarms?
description.60: You'd think that the combined forces of the Captain, D-Man, and Battlestar would be more than a match for the villainous Flag-Smasher, wouldn't you? Well, you'd be wrong! There's only one way the heroes can beat him... and that's if one of the heroes makes the ultimate sacrifice!
description.65: As Ghaur explains his origin, the Silver Surfer learns of his plot to capture the power of the Serpent Crown!
description.67: Viper's conspiracy threatens to turn drug addicts into mind-controlled soldiers, and the Punisher is next on her list of victims!
description.68: The continuing defense against the Atlantean attacks, a glimpse at Peter Parker's childhood and more stories!
description.72: Lost in the desert, the thirst-maddened Conan staggers into what he thinks is a refuge sent from the gods- but what is it really?
description.75: Spidey's clash with Boomerang on the West Coast continues, with a finale you won't believe! But he'd better get back to NYC fast, because gang wars are flaring up, and the Wolf Brothers are challenging the Kingpin!
description.76: Robbie’s parents begin to act dodgy when a skeleton is uncovered at Springdale High School…so Speedball seeks answers of his own.
description.77: THE SWORDSMAN LIVES! How has the reformed villain-turned-Avenger back from the dead? And why would he fight AGAINST the Avengers!?
description.82: Daredevil is dying. Typhoid Mary and her hired goons have beaten the hero to near-death, and only Karen can save him. If Matt remains missing a minute too late, Hell's Kitchen will lose its defender. The Human Torch joins the search for Daredevil!
description.83: Excalibur moves in together! But before they can say "team bonding exercise", the Juggernaut attacks! Cain Marko has broken out of prison and is on a rampage across Europe. But why? Can this new team take down the Unstoppable One?
description.84: It's the Hulk versus The Thing versus...another Hulk? There's only one man who can be behind this: Doctor Doom!
description.85: After several mysterious deaths of NASA astronauts, Tony Stark as Iron Man is called in to investigate. Not surprisingly, A.I.M is involved.
description.87: Prelude to Inferno! The New Mutants meet Gosamyr's family, following their escape from Spyder's lair. The Darkchilde ushers the New Mutants to Limbo.
description.88: Asgard does not stand alone--Leir and the Celtic pantheon have come to turn the tide of battle at last! Meanwhile, Thor makes a shocking discovery at the Black Pyramid!
description.92: The Thing is in the hospital after his battle with the Hulk, so Ms. Marvel decides to get payback by picking a fight with the Hulk's cousin - Jen Walters, the She-Hulk! But who is the mysterious figure watching from the shadows?
description.95: The In-Betweener attempted to kill Galactus and now the world eater is out for revenge! These two cosmic beings of immense power will battle to the death as the Silver Surfer and Fantastic Four can only watch!
description.96: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #122. ""Who Am I?"" The X-Men attend a chilling Halloween party-in masks!
description.97: Punisher meets Jason Hunt, a young man whose father was murdered alongside Frank's family. With Hector Montoya out on parole, Punisher and Jason vow to see the mobster six feet under. But complications arise- Daredevil makes an untimely appearance!

6.text: Gene and Robin, trapped in a shoot-out with The Punisher! Brandishing too many weapons for one person, Punisher invades Damage Control’s office demanding answers. Will Robin Chapel’s silver-tongued sales pitch save the day?

7.text: Namor takes heat from the original Human Torch in their first ever battle!

8.text: The alien Horde has been defeated! But are the aliens who conquered them friendly or Earth's greatest enemies yet? The Morituri Brave wants to know and she wants to know fast -- before she dies like her friends!

9.text: Meet the luckiest soldier the 'Nam's ever seen! He's come through battle after battle without a scratch, and so has his whole unit. But what happens to this lucky guy when his luck finally runs out?

10.text: Dagger adjusts to a new life without her sight. While kidnapped, Cloak comes across the previous owner of his Cloak of Darkness.

11.text: Frank Castle fortifies his forces against Kingpin by assembling his own army.

12.text: Jennifer and Wyatt head to the Keewazi reservation for their upcoming wedding. But the big day may be ruined by a mystical madman threatening to steal all female magic from the world! Plus, Jennifer and Wyatt undergo a critical shift as a couple.

13.text: A new criminal asserts his place in the city…but may actually be one of the Wolfpack member’s father!

16.text: Hawkeye has been reunited with his old partner, the Black Widow. And it's a good thing! The avenging archer is going to need all the help he can get when he faces the hordes of A.I.M.!

19.text: A super-team SMACKDOWN! The NIGHT SHIFT has come for the West Coast Avengers - and only one team will walk away!

21.text: All hail Dormammu, Sorcerer Supreme!? The dread demon has taken hold of Strange's body, and only his beloved Clea can save him!

24.text: Power Pack's parents have learned their secret identities! But that may be the least of their worries if the Pack can't defeat the Bogeyman and rescue them from the Inferno!

25.text: A new Star Brand is born! Jacob Burnley has been gifted with the Star Brand's power, but what happened to the original Star Brand, Ken Connell?

26.text: The effects of INFERNO hit the world of Spider-Man! Peter's pal Harry Osborn is in grave danger at his chemical plant!

27.text: A cat-hating supervillain turns Speedball’s world upside down in "The Two-Legged Rat"!

36.text: The New Mutants head to Limbo to take the fight straight to the demons' doorstep! Plus, Magik continues her transformation into the Darkchilde!
The New Mutants head to Limbo to take the fight straight to the demons' doorstep! Plus, Magik continues her transformation into the Darkchilde!

39.text: Manhattan has been transformed by demon magic! Inanimate objects have been given life. Subway trains are going off the rails. The Empire State Building is on a rampage. How will the X-Men be able to save anyone when everything is possessed?

Manhattan has been transformed by demon magic! Inanimate objects have been given life. Subway trains are going off the rails. The Empire State Building is on a rampage. How will the X-Men be able to save anyone when everything is possessed?

40.text: Jubilee may have bitten off more than she can chew when she agreed to join the X-Men. The teenage mutant and the X-team are in a battle for their lives at their Australian Outback base. And this time the X-men are facing the double threat of Mr. Jip and the Serpent Society!

43.text: The X-Men have found the secret location of the Marauders and head out to do battle! Plus, Rogue and Dazzler face off for Longshot's affection!
The X-Men have found the secret location of the Marauders and head out to do battle! Plus, Rogue and Dazzler face off for Longshot's affection!

44.text: Wolverine's not himself - in fact, he's possessed by the Muramasa Sword! The beast within the blade has targeted Jessica Drew, a.k.a. Spider-Woman, for sacrifice; only her best friend and a longtime enemy can save her!

46.text: An Acts of Vengeance crossover! John, Gene, and Bart are trapped in the maximum security wing of The Vault. Meanwhile, Damage Control is sold to a multi-national corporation. And that's the good news!

48.text: On a secluded island once owned by Magneto, the Deviant priest Ghaur is hard at work on a device that will enable his master to bring about the destruction of Earth -- but local photographer Peter Parker of the Daily Bugle is on the case.

52.text: The epic crossover of ATLANTIS ATTACKS pulls the armored Avengers into the fray! Tony Stark joins forces with Namor against the menace of Hydra, but one of these Avengers won't make it out of this fight alive!

54.text: Frank and Micro protect a young survivor of a home invasion.

56.text: When the Black Widow finds herself about to be snuffed by A.I.M., it's Hawkeye to the rescue!

61.text: ATLANTIS ATTACKS! Talk about your free-for-all fights! Dr. Tyrone— you know him as Tyrannus— is out to destroy Ghaur's plan. He's got a good chance in succeeding, because he's got Spider-Man under his control!

62.text: The Morituri welcome three new members. But the welcome may be very short-lived, because the government's secret anti-Morituri force is planning to make instant martyrs of the whole Strikeforce: Morituri team!

64.text: Over the past couple of years, we've seen a lot of characters finish their tours of duty and leave the 'Nam. But what happened to them next? You'll find out as we check up on Ed, Top, Rob, and all the rest in this special home-front issue!

65.text: Atlantis' war against the surface world starts here! ATLANTIS ATTACKS begins.

66.text: The Kingpin is on the Punisher’s trail, unleashing one of his newest (and deadliest) assassins to take out the one-man army!

67.text: Punisher and Moon Knight come to blows in Chapter Five of ATLANTIS ATTACKS!

68.text: This is it! Spider-Man vs. Attuma and the entire Atlantean Army in this blockbuster chapter from the ATLANTIS ATTACKS event! The Fantastic Four guest-star.

69.text: Tyrannus and his Serpent Men come for Spider-Man and Cloak and Dagger in this crossover to ATLANTIS ATTACKS!

70.text: Wyatt Wingfoot and She-Hulk are getting hitched (and the proposal totally flouts convention)! Following their engagement, Jennifer investigates some Native American artifacts that may spell danger for her and Wyatt.

71.text: A haunted house in the South Bronx doubles as a headquarters for criminals. And the Wolfpack are here to bust up their op!

73.text: Two FBI agents arrive in New York to discover what really happened during INFERNO. After X-Factor undergoes a round of questioning the team enlists the help of Reed Richards to help with their cover story.

Two FBI agents arrive in New York to discover what really happened during INFERNO. After X-Factor undergoes a round of questioning the team enlists the help of Reed Richards to help with their cover story.

74.text: Namor takes New York! Recounting the Sub-Mariner’s Big Apple adventure from Marvel Mystery #1-4!

75.text: Spidey's clash with Boomerang on the West Coast continues, with a finale you won't believe! But he'd better get back to NYC fast, because gang wars are flaring up, and the Wolf Brothers are challenging the Kingpin!

76.text: Robbie’s parents begin to act dodgy when a skeleton is uncovered at Springdale High School…so Speedball seeks answers of his own.

77.text: THE SWORDSMAN LIVES! How has the reformed villain-turned-Avenger back from the dead? And why would he fight AGAINST the Avengers!?

90.text: Cyclops' son is in danger of demon-abduction and so, with the help of Jean Grey, he sets out to rescue the boy. But with a demon horde bearing down on them, will the mutant duo be able to retrieve the child?

Cyclops' son is in danger of demon-abduction and so, with the help of Jean Grey, he sets out to rescue the boy. But with a demon horde bearing down on them, will the mutant duo be able to retrieve the child?

93.text: Jean Grey is alive! One of her teammates has known about this for quite some time, and Storm isn't too happy about it. Meanwhile, tensions near their breaking point between Psylocke and Rogue. Fists will fly!

Jean Grey is alive! One of her teammates has known about this for quite some time, and Storm isn't too happy about it. Meanwhile, tensions near their breaking point between Psylocke and Rogue. Fists will fly!

94.text: A cursed sword is seeking a kindred spirit, and a hero has already fallen prey to its evil! Is Wolverine next? Guest-starring the Silver Samurai!

98.text: As the Inferno storyline gets under way, the Bogeyman returns from Limbo... as a real Bogeyman! When he takes revenge on Power Pack in front of the kids' parents, it could blow their secret identities forever!

99.text: A young Sub-Mariner has his first brush with surface-dwellers!
